parse: Verb - Present Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: A primary verb; properly, to lead; by implication, to bring, drive, go, pass, or induce.
A primary particle of present time; 'now'; also as noun or adjective present or immediate.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Vocative Masculine Plural
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.
Today, now. Neuter of a presumed compound of the article ho and hemera; on the day; generally, now.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.
Tomorrow. From a derivative of the same as aer; properly, fresh, i.e. to-morrow.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Middle - 1st Person Plural

str2: A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
This here, this, that, he, she, it.
A city, the inhabitants of a city. Probably from the same as polemos, or perhaps from polus; a town.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: (a) I make, manufacture, construct, (b) I do, act, cause. Apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary; to make or do.
A year, cycle of time. Prolongation from a primary enos; a year.
(a) there, yonder, in that place, (b) thither, there. Of uncertain affinity; there; by extension, thither.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Middle - 1st Person Plural
str2: From en and poreuomai; to travel in, i.e. to trade.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: To gain, acquire, win (over), avoid loss. From kerdos; to gain.
